full_article:
KATHMANDU, APRIL 8

Nepal Stock Exchange (NEPSE) has announced a significant change to its trading schedule, moving to a Monday to Friday trading week effective from April 6.

googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1687249846701-0'); });

Related Articles NEPSE drops 71 points on first trading day; all sectors in red NEPSE hits second circuit breaker after 5% surge

googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1687249883356-0'); });

The change follows a Cabinet decision taken on April 5, which established a new government office schedule of 9:00 am to 5:00 pm with Saturday and Sunday as weekly public holidays.

NEPSE's board of directors, in a meeting held on the same date, resolved to align the stock exchange's trading operations with the new schedule accordingly.

googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1686127029429-0'); }); googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1686127067910-0'); }); googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1686127112906-0'); });

The shift marks a notable departure from NEPSE's longstanding practice of operating Sunday through Thursday from 11:00 am to 3:00 pm - a schedule rooted in Nepal's previous working week, which treated Sunday as a working day and Saturday as the weekly holiday.

The new arrangement brings Nepal's capital market calendar in line with global financial markets, which predominantly operate on a Monday-to-Friday schedule, and significantly extends daily trading hours. All stakeholders have been urged to take note of the revised schedule.

